last_episode_to_air.name: Stand-Up: Award Worthy Television
last_episode_to_air.overview: Six comedians - Mike Birbiglia (The Old Man and The Pool), Alex Edelman (Just For Us), Jacqueline Novak (Get on Your Knees), Jenny Slate (Seasoned Professional), Taylor Tomlinson (Have It All), Ramy Youssef (More Feelings) on what's funny today.

name: Off Script with The Hollywood Reporter
original_name: Off Script with The Hollywood Reporter
overview: THR’s famed Roundtables are reimagined for broadcast and offer a fresh perspective on a classic, showcasing the collective brilliance of the entertainment industry's finest and funniest minds as never before.

episodes.name: Songwriter
episodes.overview: Six iconic hit songwriters, Jon Batiste, Billie Eilish, Cynthia Erivo, Dua Lipa, Julia Michaels, and Olivia Rodrigo, share stories and secrets about how to make a hit songs for a movie, sources of inspiration, and their go-to karaoke bangers.

episodes.name: Actress
episodes.overview: Six of the most talented actresses in Hollywood - Annette Bening, Lily Gladstone, Greta Lee, Carey Mulligan, Margot Robbie & Emma Stone meet up for an intimate conversation about the year's biggest films and creating indelible characters on screen.

episodes.name: Director
episodes.overview: Directing a blockbuster movie takes skill, stamina and vision. Directors Blitz Bazawule, Bradley Cooper, Ava DuVernay, Greta Gerwig, Todd Haynes and Michael Mann share secrets of the art of movie making.

episodes.name: Actor
episodes.overview: Acclaimed actors Colman Domingo, Robert Downey Jr., Paul Giamatti, Mark Ruffalo, Andrew Scott and Jeffrey Wright on their first big breaks, the person they'd most want to work with and what they'd be doing if they weren't actors.

episodes.name: Producer
episodes.overview: Six top film producers - Tom Ackerley, Ed Guiney, Natalie Portman, Scott Sanders, Christine Vachon and George C. Wolfe - share behind-the-scenes stories of how movies get made and what it takes to get audiences into theaters.

episodes.name: Comedy Actress
episodes.overview: Six comedy actresses tell stories from set: Quinta Brunson, (Abbott Elementary), Michelle Buteau, (Survival of the Thickest), Renee Elise Goldsberry, (Girls5Eva), Ego Nwodim, (Saturday Night Live), Maya Rudolph, (Loot), Kristen Wiig, (Palm Royale).

episodes.name: Drama Actress: Award Worthy Television
episodes.overview: Jennifer Aniston (The Morning Show), Jodie Foster (True Detective), Brie Larson (Lessons in Chemistry), Nicole Kidman (Expats), Anna Sawai (Shogun), Sofia Vergara (Griselda), Naomi Watts (Feud) talk about their roles in this year's biggest dramas.

episodes.name: Drama Actor: Award Worthy Television
episodes.overview: Matt Bomer (Fellow Travelers), Nicholas Galitzine (Mary & George), Jon Hamm (Fargo), Clive Owen (Monsieur Spade), David Oyelowo (Lawmen: Bass Reeves), Callum Turner (Masters of the Air) cover it all from characters to pierced prosthetic nipples.

episodes.name: Comedy Actor: Award Worthy Television
episodes.overview: Funny guys John Goodman (The Righteous Gemstones), Kelsey Grammer (Frasier), Theo James (The Gentleman), Anthony Mackie (Twisted Metal), Ricky Martin (Palm Royale), Bowen Yang (Saturday Night Live) share a few laughs & some behind the scenes stories.
